No fewer than 10 corpses have been recovered after gunmen suspected to be bandits attacked Unguwar Wakili in Zango Kataf Local Government Area of Kaduna State.  In a statement, the local government authorities said a  24-hour curfew has been imposed on Ungwan Juju, Mabuhu, Ungwan Wakili and Zangon Urban with immediate effect.  “This is to allow men of the Nigerian Army to restore peace on that axis,” Yabo Chris Ephraim,Special Assistant (Media) to Chairman ,Zangon Kataf Local Government Council of Kaduna State said.  The Police in Kaduna were yet to react to the incident.  Details Shortly…